Class
Description
AddElementCommand
Command that adds a new human element to the collection.
App
The main application class for running the space collection manager.
AverageOfImpactSpeedCommand
Command that calculates the average of impact speeds of all humans in the collection.
ClearCommand
A command that removes all elements from the collection.
CLIClient
CLIClient is a class that implements command-line interaction with the user.
CLICommand
A basic class for all commands that use a CLIClient as a receiver.
CollectionCommand
Basic class of all commands, that use CollectionManager as receiver.
CommandNotFoundError
Exception thrown when the CLI client cannot find a command by its trigger.
ExecuteCommand
A command that executes specified script with commands.
ExitCommand
ExitCommand is a CLICommand that exits the program
FilterByImpactSpeed
A command that shows humans whose impact speed is greater than the specified value.
HeadCommand
This command returns the first element of the collection.
HelpCommand
HelpCommand is a CLICommand that shows a list of all registered commands with their descriptions and static requirements
HistoryCommand
Show list of all previously executed commands
InfoCommand
This command shows information about the collection.
InlineParamsError
Exception thrown when the number of inline parameters is not equal to the expected number of command static requirements.
PrintSortedCommand
A command that prints humans from collection sorted by impact speed.
RandomCommand
Adds a randomly generated human with various fields to the collection
RemoveByIdCommand
This command removes an element from the collection by ID.
RemoveFirstCommand
This command removes the first element from the collection.
RemoveLastCommand
This command removes the last element from the collection.
SafeLineInput
A supplier that provides user input from the command line in a safe way.
SaveCommand
A command that saves the collection to a file.
SetFuzzyCommand
Change fuzzy search mode
ShowCommand
A command that displays information about the collection.
TailCommand
A command that displays the last element of the collection.
TextColor
Used for coloring text in console.
